# general
C-x is special: prefix for different things
C-x C-s save
C-x C-c exit
C-g abort running/started command
C-h k [command] show help

# moving
C-v next screen/page
M-v prev screen/page
C-l move screen around cursor
C-p up (previous)
C-b left (backwards)
C-n down (next)
C-f right (forward)
M-b word left (backwards)
M-f word right (forward)
C-a line beginning
C-e line ending
M-a sentence beginning
M-e sentence ending
M-< document beginning
M-> document ending

# numbers: prefix arguments
- C-3p down (next) for 3 lines up
- or C-u 3 C-p, C-u stores the number
- some commands use arguments as flags

# windows (in emacs)
- C-x 1 kills all other windows
